Tammy Petersen, News24Taxis. (Duncan Alfreds, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - The body of a 28-year-old taxi driver was found inside a taxi in Dobsonville on Saturday, police confirm.The man, identified as Themba Halalisani Zondi, had sustained gunshot wounds, spokesperson Captain Mpande Khoza said in a statement.The discovery was made in the early hours of this morning on Elias Motswaledi Road.&ldquo;According to witnesses, the vehicle in which the deceased was found was seen earlier today parked next to the road. His body was noticed by a pedestrian who was on his way to work.&rdquo;The driver was last seen by the owner of the vehicle on Friday.&ldquo;The motive for the murder is unknown,&rdquo; Khoza saidA case of murder is being investigated.No arrests have yet been made.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.